<br>
So here are a couple of ideas for a correction.  I'm just throwing them out to get some feedback.<br>
<br>
The first involves a couple of new disciplines.  Along the lines of a Warrior's current aggressive and evasive.  If we say a Warrior's normal mitigation/damage output is expressed as 100%/100% and we say that a Knights normal mitigation/damage output compared to a Warrior would be 95%/80% (I grant that some may argue on the 95% mitigation figure of a Knight compared to a Warrior.  And others will argue that Knights aren't just doing 80% of a Warrior's damage in the high end, but for the sake of discussion, lets agree these figures are correct).<br>
<br>
Now the currently when a Warrior uses defensive, these values change to something like 140%/60% (that is, he gets hit for 40% less damage but does about 40% less damage as a result).  <br>
<br>
The new defense type discipline would be more along the lines of 120%/80% for a Warrior.  And Knights would get a version that is along the lines of 105%/70% (remember, these percentages are based on the Warrior normal 100%/100%, so the Knights would move from their normal mitigation of 95% to 105%, a 10% improvement in mitigation, while losing 10% in damage output).<br>
<br>
The timer on these disciplines would be five minutes and would last five minutes.  Basically, you could keep it active indefinetly, if you so choose, but it would require you to fire it off every 5 minutes.<br>
<br>
The second discipline would be offensive in nature.  What it would do is change these figures to 80%/120% for a Warrior and 85%/90% for a Knight.  It would have the same timer and duration as the defense version.  Meaning you could flip flop them every 5 minutes.   The offense disciplines would help put the damage dealt by the plate melee more in line with where it should be in comparison to that done by Monks/Rogues, but at the expense of mitigation.  This would be used by non-MT plate melee.<br>
<br>
The first would mean that a Warrior would be the best choice for uber boss mob tank, even in those situations where defensive isn't desireable, but in a pinch a Knight would work as well (hopefully).  It also means that given much superior gear, a Knight might be the better choice.  Certainly they would be a better choice than a Monk.  The second would help balance the current damage imbalance, but at a price.<br>
<br>
This would leave defensive alone, since there is a time and a place where its needed.  But it would also give both Warriors and Knights clear superiority as meat shields both in groups and tanking uber mobs.  It would 'balance' things a bit better, but not with a new defense table, but with disciplines only gained at level 60, where the imbalance truly begins to show.  Defensive has already shown it can be done, and it shouldn't take major reworking of code to do it.<br>
<br>
Final idea.  This would be a new AAXP ability for Warriors.  There would need to be 2 or 3 levels to it.  It would an ability you could fire off which caused the Warrior to proc an enraging blow type attack.  The duration could be set for 3 or 5 minutes and would refresh in something like 10 minutes.  As each level in the ability was aquired, it would proc more frequently.   The idea here is, not every Warrior in the game is going to be able to get ahold of enraging blow weapons.  But every Warrior in the game SHOULD be able to do their job respectably without them, this would be another tool towards that end.  And it would be no more trivializing to the game than allowing enraging blow weapons to drop to begin with.  If its not trivial with enraging blow weapons on a few Warriors, it shouldn't be trivial having more Warriors with a similar ability.<br>
<br>
This would also help counter balance the spell improvements that Knights are/will receive in the near future (I just can't believe that Verant won't be improving Paladin heals in some fashion). <br>
