<br>
I'm seeing SK's (Probably pallies too, but I see SK's more) who are able to keep aggro better then me, and the cheal chain, supported by modrod 2, can keep them alive.<br>
<br>
From NToV to Ssra, which is what my guild finds challanging and do-able.<br>
<br>
The SK's keep aggro better, which means the raid as a whole can up DPS, and kill faster.<br>
<br>
In fact, the faster kill, means that the SK sometimes actually takes LESS!! mana to heal then the warrior. Not less mana per second, of course, but less mana total, because the fight lasts much longer with a defefensive warrior.<br>
<br>
Yes, this means that warriors are better tanks when mana is an issue, especially if the fight lasts less then 3 miniutes, but that isn't the case, I see, in many NToV/Ssra enounters. Curse takes us betweeen 30-45 miniutes with a warrior, depending on who shows up, and we can shave almost 30% !!!!! off that by using a SK tank and more nuking (Ok, best case scenerio- Usually we only save a few miniutes).<br>
<br>
This is with a warrior with EB off AoW and the SoD2 off Cursed Cycle. (Sorry, drunk ATM, EB off AoW is Blade of Carnage, forget the named of the sword off Cursed cycle with the enchanter nuke).<br>
<br>
Warriors are NOT as good as SK's in higher end encounters, and will not be unless our taunt is upgraded in some manner.<br>
<br>
Yes, I realize, that upping our taunt in this manner might overpower us in terms of breaking into Kael or other encounters that more players are actually at in the game.<br>
<br>
Well, find a way to make us the best tanks in the end game without overpowering us in the almost end game, (assuming you consider Ssra and ST the end game, which really, it isn't, but from what I've heard, it gets worse past that), or find a niche for us that ISN'T where we are supposed to be the best tank anytime.<br>
<br>
Notice, I'm NOT saying invalidate SK's or Pallies as a tank class.  They tank (absorb damage) FINE, but they have a massive amount of taunt that we can't compete with.\<br>
<br>
Let pallies and SK tank EXP groups. Let them tank raids. I don't care about that. Just make it a toss up between bringing another warrior or bringing another pally to a raid. IE, I have 2 level 60 equally equipped equal AAXP point war or pally/sk on the same account- I want to be told, bring either, both add the same value to the raid. NOT don't bring the warrior, we don't need him.<br>
<br>
Right now, in the game I am playing, it is MORE desirable to bring my 53!!! Mage then my 60 warrior. I beleive that this is wrong. This is Ssra and NToV where people under 58 (In my experiance) are not even allowed normally!<br>
